d expect it to change, but beyond that, I am all for change if 343 can make an awesome new game. It was also announced that Halo 4 would be the start of a new trilogy and that the enemies would not be mainly Covenant or Flood. Ubisoft showed off the kick ass Splinter Cell: Black List. Then EA showed off sports games. Now let me take a second here to note that I have never understood these. I hate sports games. They not only seem entirely pointless, boring, and unrealistic, but why not just kick a ball around irl? Regardless, EA unveiled Madden and FIFA ’13. Trailers were also aired for the new Fable, a stupid installment in an already dead series: Gears: Judgement, what looks to be an awesome racing game - Forza: Horizon, Nike+Kinect (again, who cares?), South Park, and awesome game called Matter, Ascension, Tomb Raider, Resident Evil 6, COD: Black Ops 2, and tons more. They also announced a lot of things for the XBox Live experience in general, mainly revolving around broadcast sports and cable TV partnerships. Music was touched upon, but not really discussed. However, SmartGlass looks pretty awesome and like a far superior idea to the WiiU’s take. SmartGlass allows the user to download an app on their smartphone or tablet, currently only on Windows Marketplace and hopefully coming to iOS or Android, and have this work either as a remote for the XBox or as an extension of the game itself, much as the WiiU’s GamePad does.\r\n\r\nhttp://youtu.be/5N-CRrP9xjQ\r\n\r\nSony’s conference launched with a trailer for Beyond Two Souls. This looks stunningly awesome, sadly I don’t own a PS3 so I won’t be getting a taste of this on my own. Sony announced a PSVita version of AllStars Battle Royale with support for cross-platform gaming and a COD title for it called Black Ops: Declassified. A special version of Assassin’s Creed III was announced for the PSVita as well. Wonderbook with AR looked pretty stupid. It’s basically a book with a ton of QR codes and motion tracked points so games and “stories” can come to life. However, there will be a Harry Potter launch title for it. God of War: Ascension was announced for a spring 2013 release. Sony wrapped up with an awesome demo of The Last of Us.\r\n\r\nhttp://youtu.be/ZJmjXBXn9zY\r\n\r\nLater on, EA showed off an awesome looking DeadSpace 3 and expansions for BattleField 3. I was and am confused by a third installment in DeadSpace this as I thought he died at the end of DS2? Alas. I assume they will work in some sort of lame resurrection story. Need For Speed: Most Wanted was announced, EA got the rights to UFC and there will be new DLCs for Star Wars: The Old Republic.\r\n\r\nhttp://youtu.be/83qSiBcA7Yg\r\n\r\nUbisoft was the unexpected sucker punch. They showed off a ton of WiiU games such as Rayman Legends, Rabbids Land and a couple others.Nearly everything else compares to an awesome new game that came from nowhere: Watchdogs. This combines all awesome things: hackers, assassins, guns, and awesomeness.\r\n\r\nNintendo intro’ed their next console: the WiiU. Their showed off the “Pro Controller” which is basically an XBox 360 controller for the WiiU: this would be for those of us who would prefer not to have a large screen below us, like one huge DS. They also said that the tablet controller, dubbed the GamePad, would have dual analog sticks along with onboard NFC and a way to act as a standard TV remote. Nintendo’s conference seemed rather… meh to me. They showcased a new game and announced that the WiiU will now be able to support two GamePads (the things with the touch screens). MiiVerse was announced as a WiiU-centric social network where people can send texts, hand written notes, see each other’s miis and much more. Eventually access to this will expand to the DS, smartphones and computers. Super Mario Bros U was announced, but, again, looks rather meh with some social networking built in. In a collection like game, there were hints at Samus getting a chance at the WiiU (which would be boss).\r\n\r\nWhile I am still not convinced that the WiiU is a legitimate console, it will have Batman: Arkham City Armored Edition as an exclusive. Scribblenauts. Lego City. Just Dance. ZombiU. There were a bunch of things that didn’t really matter that launched on the 3DS. However, the WiiU will be getting MassEffect 3.\r\n\r\nFor all intents and purposes, that was the end of E3. The third day had a lot of really cool games, but the coolest and best were showcased in the first couple days. However, there are really two games that stole the show and I look forward to the most: Dishonored and <del>Border</del>Dubsteplands 2. (P.S. Yes I realize there wasn''t much of a presence of Dishonored at E3, don''t whine).\r\n\r\nhttp://youtu.be/IyDvT7XpaBc\r\n\r\nDishonored looks amazing. That’s really all I can say and link you to the trailer. The new Borderlands 2 trailer was awesome and I look forward to more guns and wubwub. Also, the new character called Zer0 looks to be an awesome update to Mordecai. Also, before you ask, the epic build up music is Nero''s Doomsday.\r\n\r\nhttp://youtu.be/kKVf5feSMEg\r\n\r\nSource: <a href="http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/06/09/e3-2012-in-15-minutes"><strong><em>IGN</em></strong></a>', 'The Past Two Weeks: E3 & WWDC [E3 Edition]', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '80-revision-9', '', '', '2012-06-15 03:01:21', '2012-06-15 03:01:21', '', 80, 'http://www.slushie.me/2012/90/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
