(304, 2, '2012-12-04 21:29:49', '2012-12-05 02:29:49', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAt the conclusion of the Chiefs 27-21 victory over the Carolina Panthers, there must have been a bitter sweet feeling. In the wake of the death of Jovan Blecher a starting linebacker for the Chiefs, they endured a difficult contest against the Panthers and were able to snap their eight game losing streak.\r\nAccording to some analyst, however there is a bigger issue looming. Should the NFL have allowed the game to continue on as scheduled in light of these events? For the Chiefs players themselves the answer was yes, and after a moment of silence the Chiefs put out their best performance of the year. During a season where fans have died claiming the Chief’s ineptitude as the cause, it must have been nice for Chiefs fans watching the game today. A plane usually flying overhead to endorse the firing of GM Scott Pioli was absent. Chiefs fans usually decked out in black to protest the team’s struggles showed up in red.\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/443fa06424e34ff489e196aa7b2ee085-c76a812dcc8545c895f73bf02615b18e-3.jpeg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-301" title="Sign at Cheifs/Panthers game." src="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/443fa06424e34ff489e196aa7b2ee085-c76a812dcc8545c895f73bf02615b18e-3-857x1024.jpeg" alt="Fan holds up sign at Cheifs/Panthers game." width="288" height="344" /></a></p>\r\nWhile Brady Quinn’s job in Kansas City maybe conclude at the end of this season, he deserves praise for his work today. Quinn threw for 201 yards on 23 attempts gaining an 83% completion rating; Quinn also threw two touchdowns. Jamaal Charles continues his recent resurgence today, gaining 127 yards on 27 carries.<a href="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/156941966.0_standard_352.0.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-278" src="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/156941966.0_standard_352.0-300x199.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a>Regardless of the future for the Kansas City Chiefs, which may or may not involve the number one draft pick this year, the effort today shows a wonderful resilience and mental toughness about the team. It also shows that the world doesn’t always revolve around football and that there is a larger life outside of the game.', 'Chiefs'' Emotional Win on Sunday', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '274-revision-22', '', '', '2012-12-04 21:29:49', '2012-12-05 02:29:49', '', 274, 'http://www.slushie.me/304/274-revision-22/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
