(400, 8, '2013-01-13 16:41:28', '2013-01-13 21:41:28', 'Well darn, after a petition 34,000 strong was offered to the United States government it seems that a U.S. made Death Star will not be in the works. The idea of the petition was that the creation of such a weapon would not only spur national defense but also stimulate the economy and create jobs. Paul Shawcross White House advisor on science and space, claims that the 850 quadrillion dollar project is out of line with the White House''s plans. The Obama administration, "does not support blowing up planets". This is a crushing blow to supporters and those wishing to thrust the U.S. into total military dominance. With looming changes coming to our current political landscape, it appears that a Death Star is not in the future.', 'Senate says no to Death Star petition', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '347-revision', '', '', '2013-01-13 16:41:28', '2013-01-13 21:41:28', '', 347, 'http://www.slushie.me/400/347-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
