(473, 8, '2013-02-25 13:42:40', '2013-02-25 18:42:40', 'Keeping with these Star Wars themed articles I''ve been writing I figured I should give this a whirl as well(If you haven''t seen my Death Star article <a href="http://slushie.me/347">please do</a>).  Recently a court has come to the decision that the New York Yankees are the only team that can use the name "Evil Empire" in baseball. How did this crazy situation come up you ask? A company named Evil Enterprises Inc has been trying to become "Baseball''s Evil Empire" since 2008.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_474" align="alignleft" width="350"]<a href="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/OB-WL536_vader_G_20130222162933.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-474 " alt="Getty Images" src="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/OB-WL536_vader_G_20130222162933.jpg" width="350" height="233" /></a> Getty Images[/caption]\r\n\r\nWould they seize the flailing Astros and steer them to the path of dark success? Sadly no this only means that they would be able to sell merchandise with the logo. Anyone who knows baseball knows that the Yankees are the Evil Empire, and those who don''t <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e-oUIuYTvWc">do now</a>. As a result, the MLB stepped in on the teams behalf and the two sides have been fighting over this issue for nearly four years now. In the end however it seems that the Yankees have won. Judges have said "In short, the record shows that there is only one Evil Empire in baseball and it is the <a id="yui_3_5_1_23_1361769727428_485" href="http://sports.yahoo.com/mlb/teams/nyy">New York Yankees</a>," wrote the judges. "Accordingly, we find that [the Yankees] have a protectable trademark right in the term . . . as used in connection with baseball." While Yankees fans might be a little upset with the term being used for their team, it seems that the team has fully embraced the persona.', 'The Yankees are baseball''s only Evil Empire.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-yankees-are-baseballs-only-evil-empire', '', '', '2013-02-25 18:14:02', '2013-02-25 23:14:02', '', 0, 'http://www.slushie.me/?p=473', 0, 'post', '', 0),
