on the Retina Displays. This display is crazy. Like almost no point to it crazy. But there is a point: it can be done.\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>The Wrap Up</strong></p>\r\nIf you are a TL;DR person or just in a TL;DR mood, then feel free to just read the first and last paragraphs, jerk. Running Jelly Bean, this is almost without a doubt the most powerful phone on the market right now. However, it isn''t the best phone. Lacking some key features like LTE, expandable memory, and a good UI the Find 5 can''t be the top dog. It can still rank. But with a big price tag, it probably won''t be. If you want a good looking, powerful, light phone that is the Android equivalent of an iPhone, go for this one.\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Two last things. I can''t help but think that the Find 5''s name is a publicity stunt. Sure it can be argued that it has a 5" display, but it seems more to me like it is trying to get some search results from "iPhone 5." I can''t resist. OPPO Find Style.<a href="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mbbxettdRA1rcdbkgo1_1280.gif"><img class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mbbxettdRA1rcdbkgo1_1280.gif" width="600" height="720" /></a></p>', 'Only Dark Wizardry Could Jam This Much Into A Smartphone (Oppo Find 5)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '492-revision-10', '', '', '2013-02-28 14:57:32', '2013-02-28 19:57:32', '', 492, 'http://www.slushie.me/507/492-revision-10/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
