(552, 8, '2013-05-16 19:15:11', '2013-05-17 00:15:11', 'With the Chicago Bulls and Oklahoma City Thunder knocked out of the playoffs the Conference Finals are looking a little clearer. Tonight will determine who the Heat and Grizzlies face off against in the Eastern and Western Conference Finals respectively.\r\n\r\nTonight, the Golden State Warriors and New York Knicks both find themselves with their backs against the wall in their respective series. It''s not out of the question for either team to make a comeback but for one team, it''s less than likely. Right now, we''re going to decide which teams are going into the Finals, and which teams will be out.\r\n\r\n<strong>New York Knicks</strong>: <strong>IN</strong>                  Indiana Pacers: Out<strong><a href="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/hi-res-7349466_crop_exact.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-554 alignleft" alt="hi-res-7349466_crop_exact" src="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/hi-res-7349466_crop_exact.jpg" width="480" height="320" /></a></strong>\r\n\r\nIn the past two games the Knicks have scored 27% and 28% from the three point line. If they want to turn this series around they need somebody to get out of their shooting slump and get back in shape. With Carmelo Anthony, Raymond Felton, and reigning Sixth Man of the Year J.R Smith in tow, this seems totally possible. To add to that the, Knicks are going back to Madison Square Garden where they have outscored the Pacers in the fourth quarter 63-34 in this series.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>San Antonio Spurs:IN                 </strong>Golden State Warriors: In\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_553" align="alignleft" width="650"]<a href="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/hi-res-168753463_crop_650.jpg"><img class="wp-image-553 " alt="hi-res-168753463_crop_650" src="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/hi-res-168753463_crop_650.jpg" width="650" height="433" /></a> Ronald Martinez/Getty Images[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: center">After a 44 point outburst in Game 1, Stephen Curry and the Warriors have been relatively quiet. Part of this is the strong defense by the Spurs, and part of it is the inefficient shooting from Klay Thompson, Jarrett Jack, and company. Spurs guard Tony Parker''s incredible play as of late can''t help either, so it''s very difficult to see the Warriors surviving this last game. The only thing that might make it possible for Golden State to win is the incredible atmosphere at Oracle Arena working in their favor.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center">If things go as planned then we should be seeing the grinding defense of the Grizzlies going up against the incredibly balanced Spurs, and the dominant Heat against a Knicks team that''s supposedly designed to beat them. However as we all know, ANYTHING can happen.</p>', 'NBA Playoffs: Finishing off Round two', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nba-playoffs-finishing-off-round-two', '', '', '2013-05-16 19:15:11', '2013-05-17 00:15:11', '', 0, 'http://www.slushie.me/?p=552', 0, 'post', '', 0),
