t-align: center">After a 44 point outburst in Game 1, Stephen Curry and the Warriors have been relatively quiet. Part of this is the strong defense by the Spurs, and part of it is the inefficient shooting from Klay Thompson, Jarrett Jack, and company. Spurs guard Tony Parker''s incredible play as of late can''t help either, so it''s very difficult to see the Warriors surviving this last game. The only thing that might make it possible for Golden State to win is the incredible atmosphere at Oracle Arena working in their favor.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center">If things go as planned then we should be seeing the grinding defense of the Grizzlies going up against the incredibly balanced Spurs, and the dominant Heat against a Knicks team that''s supposedly designed to beat them. However as we all know, ANYTHING can happen.</p>', 'NBA Playoffs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '552-revision-2', '', '', '2013-05-16 19:09:17', '2013-05-17 00:09:17', '', 552, 'http://www.slushie.me/557/552-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
