gled solution is to go and survey internet and phones, and you wouldn''t be barking up the wrong tree. If you aren''t doing anything wrong, what''s to worry about?\n\nA lot.  You see, people can''t always determine what''s wrong or right.  For example, a Movie Critic might say that a certain movie is bad.  Another might say it''s a good movie.  It''s all objective.  And certainly there are things that we can denote as being actually bad, or at least, what society as a whole has deemed bad (things like Murder and Stealing).  But what if someone killed your fam', 'NSA Rant (Part 1)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '600-revision', '', '', '2013-07-22 20:48:31', '2013-07-23 01:48:31', '', 600, 'http://www.slushie.me/601/600-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(613, 2, '2013-08-23 15:45:11', '2013-08-23 20:45:11', 'Granted, that is a sweeping statement, but you''ll see what I mean.\r\n\r\nTake a look at the Firefly intro from 2002.\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/D7vS4z6ngQo" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\nNow take a look at the Breaking Bad intro from 2008.\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/HEmx23LwFhI" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\nCould Breaking Bad have taken a page out of Firefly''s book with the sweeping, funky bass guitar?\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Firefly_1x07_Jaynestown_254.sized_.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-606 aligncenter" alt="No, not that Book." src="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Firefly_1x07_Jaynestown_254.sized_.jpg" width="560" height="315" /></a></p>\r\nI don''t know, but it is interesting just how similar the two are. What if the two shows had swapped directors? Wouldn''t that be interesting.', 'TV Show Theme Sequences are Surprisingly Similar', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '605-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-23 15:45:11', '2013-08-23 20:45:11', '', 605, 'http://www.slushie.me/613/605-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
