(626, 2, '2011-10-31 20:38:33', '2011-11-01 01:38:33', '<em>by </em><strong>Tucker Chapin</strong>\r\n\r\n<img title="Mac Pro" alt="" src="http://www.burnhamwebsite.com/wp-content/gallery/mac-pro/mac-pro.png" width="603" height="380" />The deliciously powerful Cupertino monster has just come up to the chopping block in a new rumor. And it makes sense. Apple has been moving away from desk-based computing and more mobile solutions. Not to mention that of late, their desktop sales have been falling with the rise of the iPad and MacBook alternatives. Even when someone buys a desktop, they tend to go for the MacMini or the more stylish and powerful iMac. Fewer still sink their teeth into the beast known as the Mac Pro. Not to mention that its starting price is extremely expensive, but due to stereotypes, most people who need that kind of computational power tend to stray towards Linux or Windows machines just because of the stigma associated with Macs and interface interference.\r\n\r\n<img title="More..." alt="" src="https://tuckerwchapindotwordpressdotcom.wordpress.com/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/wordpress/img/trans.gif" />Another reason this would make sense is because we have been seeing rumors of Apple burgeoning yet more markets. With rumors of the <a title="iTV" href="http://9to5mac.com/2011/10/31/itv-gets-mocked-up/?utm_source=pulsenews&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+9To5Mac-MacAllDay+%289+to+5+Mac+-+Apple+Intelligence%29">iTV</a>, the next line of powerful yet slim MacBooks and possibly other categories, Apple has been cutting off balls and chains. The iPod Classic is a great example of this. People were still buying them and Apple had the choice to offer more expensive and lower storage solid-state drives in the next-gen or cut them completely. They took the financially and sensibly smarter of the two options. Who''s to say that the same can''t happen with the Mac Pro line?\r\n\r\n<em>Source: </em><a title="MacRumors" href="http://www.macrumors.com/2011/10/31/apple-questioning-the-future-of-its-mac-pro-line/?utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=pulsenews" target="_blank">MacRumors</a>', 'No Mo'' Mac Pro?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'no-mo-mac-pro', '', '', '2013-10-21 20:57:41', '2013-10-22 01:57:41', '', 0, 'http://www.slushie.me/?p=626', 0, 'post', '', 0),
