(630, 2, '2013-10-31 21:17:49', '2013-11-01 02:17:49', 'Americans really like to pick teams. Why do you think sports is such a big industry in our country? I''m not saying this is bad. Being able to rally behind a cause, totally and fully, can be very good in some instances, such as independence or equality or other stuff. When it leads to stupid shit like the Mac vs. PC argument and the Republican vs. Democrat argument is when it is a bad thing.\r\n\r\nOur national legislative system is messed up to to this. People lack the ability of self reflection and compromise. It has become a team sport about which side wins, not about arguing out points, pros, and cons until a decent and basically unanimous bill or other item is created. This is the point of a republic, or a representative democracy.  When people are so tied to a team rather than what it was originally established to accomplish, it is clear why so many religions are hard set against the warship of false idols: you begin placing your allegiance with that object or team rather than the philosophy or ideas it represents.\r\n\r\nThe Mac vs. PC argument is dumb for so many reasons. I''ll just take two. The first is simply my own irritation with the phrasing. What most people mean when they say "Mac vs. PC" or anything of the ilk, is "Mac OS vs. Windows" or "Apple vs. Windows Machines." Instead they use it to compare ANY Apple products to ANYthing running Windows. That bugs me, either use it correctly or alter it so that you are. But I digress, there will be no stopping or changing people''s ignorance or making them care (as well they maybe shouldn''t). The main reason it is so dumb is because WHO CARES. Sure, Mac OS is better at some things and Windows is better at other things. Each has great benefits and each has major problems. Thats the reason for software updates. No one is supposed to think ANY software is ever complete, done, or finalized. Sure, a game can be released, but there will still be a multitude of issues with it and sequels will be made fixing these issues and creating others. People are notoriously bad at self-criticism. People who are "Macs" and people who are "PCs" tend to not acknowledge the issues and flaws of their own system, while there clearly are. The other aspect of this argument that bothers me is the hardware driven side. Apple vs. Windows Machines. This is just as stupid as iOS vs. Android or iDevies vs. Other Smartphones. While Apple''s products do tend to be on the expensive side, the majority of this is due to the way they are marketed. There are no "low-end" Apple products. There are cheaper ones but they are all decent. Simply the point at which an Apple product starts, say 2k is frequently cheaper than a common Windows machine upgraded to the point where all of its specifications are as good as the Mac''s. This is mainly due to Apple''s system of vertical production control, but whatever. My point still stands.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/mac-vs-linux-vs-win.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-642" alt="mac-vs-linux-vs-win" src="http://www.slushie.me/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/mac-vs-linux-vs-win.jpg" width="400" height="178" /></a>\r\n\r\nMy main goal in pointing this out is to show that both Windows and Mac OS are fantastic systems, but not without their own draw-backs. Which one you PREFER is solely up to you and your discretion. It is all a matter of preference, neither is truly better or worse than the other and never will be. Also, I am not above this. I do tend to get into these arguments with people, but I do my best to keep in mind what I have mentioned above and separate my "team" from its morals or reasoning. Don''t forget about Linux.', 'Why Mac vs. PC And Other Arguments Are So Stupid', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-mac-vs-pc-and-other-arguments-are-so-stupid', '', '', '2014-07-27 11:30:13', '2014-07-27 16:30:13', '', 0, 'http://www.slushie.me/?p=630', 0, 'post', '', 0),
