That bugs me, either use it correctly or alter it so that you are. But I digress, there will be no stopping or changing people''s ignorance or making them care (as well they maybe shouldn''t). The main reason it is so dumb is because WHO CARES. Sure, Mac OS is better at some things and Windows is better at other things. Each has great benefits and each has major problems. Thats the reason for software updates. No one is supposed to think ANY software is ever complete, done, or finalized. Sure, a game can be released, but there will still be a multitude of issues with it and sequels will be made fixing these issues and creating others. People are notoriously bad at self-criticism. People who are "Macs" and people who are "PCs" tend to not acknowledge the issues and flaws of their own system, while there clearly are. The other aspect of this argument that bothers me is the hardware driven side. Apple vs. Windows Machines. This is just as stupid as iOS vs. Android or iDevies vs. Other Smartphones. While Apple''s products do tend to be on the expensive side, the majority of this is due to the way they are marketed. There are no "low-end" Apple products. There are cheaper ones but they are all decent. Simply the point at which an Apple product starts, say 2k is frequently cheaper than a common Windows machine upgraded to the point where all of its specifications are as good as the Mac''s. This is mainly due to Apple''s system of vertical production control, but whatever. My point still stands.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bobado.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/350height/image_upload/linux-microsoft-mac.jpg"><img title="Mac v PC v Linux" alt="" src="http://bobado.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/350height/image_upload/linux-microsoft-mac.jpg" width="547" height="400" /></a>\r\n\r\nMy main goal in pointing this out is to show that both Windows and Mac OS are fantastic systems, but not without their own draw-backs. Which one you PREFER is solely up to you and your discretion