(632, 2, '2011-11-04 16:01:56', '2011-11-04 21:01:56', '<em>by </em><strong>Tucker Chapin</strong>\r\n\r\nLast week I went to see In Time with Justin Timberlake, Amanda Seyfried, Olivia Wilde and <del>that dude who played Scarecrow in Batman Begins</del> Cillian Murphy. Oh, and Bryce Larkin from Chuck (Matt Bomer), Leonard Hofstadter from The Big Bang Theory (Johnny Galecki) and the guy from I Am Number Four and Beastly (Alex Pettyfer). Pretty good cast. Substantially good movie. Pretty cool premise, but does the entire movie not seem like an allegory to Occupy Wall Street? Anyhoo, the movie was both quick-paced and thoughtful at the same time. They also did an interesting thing with not making the ghettos racially broken down. This is a lame review of a pretty darn good movie (not the best by any means, but definitely something you should see) simply because analyzing it would require me spoiling much of the plot. Maybe I''ll do a breakdown in a month or so. Or not.', 'In Time', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'in-time', '', '', '2013-10-21 21:01:08', '2013-10-22 02:01:08', '', 0, 'http://www.slushie.me/?p=632', 0, 'post', '', 0),
