(634, 2, '2011-11-08 10:01:18', '2011-11-08 15:01:18', '<em>by </em><strong>Tucker Chapin</strong>\r\n\r\nI was actually kinda looking forward to iTunes Match; it seemed like a good service and Apple''s capacity for near-seamless multimedia integration is delightful. At the WWDC this past summer, Cupertino announced that it would be out by October. Well, now we are a bit late, following in the path of the 4S are we now? I surely hope it will be out by the end of 2011, as there is only so long the "native" (those are scare-quotes, not standard ones) Google Music Beta app can sustain my cloud music streaming needs and I''m too cheap for Spotify. $25 bucks a year is a pretty darn great price, so I guess they have some room. Not to mention the fact that the newest iPhone was late, so looking at that we may be looking at a February release of Match. Great. Exactly when I don''t want to be outside away from my house.', 'What Happened to iTunes Match?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-happened-to-itunes-match', '', '', '2013-10-21 21:02:31', '2013-10-22 02:02:31', '', 0, 'http://www.slushie.me/?p=634', 0, 'post', '', 0),
