(636, 2, '2011-11-08 10:13:41', '2011-11-08 15:13:41', '<em>by </em><strong>Tucker Chapin</strong><img title="Panasonic Toughpad" alt="" src="http://www-bgr-com.vimg.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/panasonic-a1.jpg" width="652" height="471" />\r\n\r\nPanasonic is releasing two more awesomely indestructible devices. We have seen their ToughBooks, now they unveil the ToughPads. Two to be exact. One in a 10" flavor that will be available first and the other in a 7" flavor. Not only can it withstand being dropped from 4 feet, being in 122° F, and has a nice rugged exterior, but it has some seriously powerful insides. A 1.2 GHz dual-core processor, 1 GB of RAM, 16 GB of onboard storage and an expansion SD card slot, Android 3.2 (Honeycomb), 10 hour battery life, removable battery, GPS, 4G LTE, Bluetooth, WiFi hotspot, and an actual physical lock*. This is like the Grave Digger of tablets. The only thing making everyone not own one of these immediately is its price tag. This bad boy will set you back $1300.\r\n\r\n*Those specs are for the 10" variety, as is the price. The 7" is a bit farther off and specs haven''t been officially released yet.', 'Finally, A Tablet That Won''t Give Me an Aneurysm If I Drop It', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'finally-a-tablet-that-wont-give-me-an-aneurysm-if-i-drop-it', '', '', '2013-10-21 21:03:40', '2013-10-22 02:03:40', '', 0, 'http://www.slushie.me/?p=636', 0, 'post', '', 0),
